CSSWAF is a proof-of-concept anti-bot web application firewall that uses CSS to detect bots by analyzing the loading order of hidden images. It also employs honeypot techniques, such as invisible links and non-loading images, to further identify and block malicious bots. This project is intended for demonstration purposes only and should not be used in production environments.

The repository provides the official implementation of the BiRefNet model.
